The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 24 November is 302,710 (34,889.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 19 November, there were 324 new confirmed cases (37.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 November, there were 372 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 13% (48 fewer cases).
